caption: This is truly the best breakfast/lunch spot in Chicago. I’ve been coming here for years and always get amazing service from Pam and Marilyn. Not to mention they are pretty fast with bringing your food. Today, for the re-grand opening I had the pleasure of meeting with the owner and she made me feel so welcomed! Check them out if you get the chance. It’s a hidden gem in Chicago’s Lincoln Park neighborhood.
Came for breakfast and no one was there. Their website says they are open. We even spoke to someone on the phone the day before and they told us they were open.
What a great brunch spot! Perfect way to spend a weekend morning! The takeout tastes just as fantastic at home...but I still miss fancy Coffees and the great atmosphere!
My friends and I had a reservation at 6:30 PM on a Friday and we were running a bit late, but they were nice enough to keep our table. Their decor is really cute and has a nice hip ambiance.
Sort of a diner atmosphere with a friendly staff. Definitely a decent place for breakfast.

Delicious. Start with something sweet and share it with the table. BYOB and they provide the mixers. The aesthetic is clean, cute and vintage/modern. Excellent staff and quick service. Good for groups or just you and someone else.
Cool place
Finest food, welcoming staff members, regularly great mood. They charge affordable rates and the food quality is awesome. Keep up the good work.
For breakfast.

I would give a zero if I could. Horrible customer service. Came in here with my husband and little daughter, Sunday around 2:15 pm. The place closes at like 3 or 3:30 pm. We were placed next to a table with a very noisy crowd. I asked the manager if we could be moved to a vacant table in the far away corner, because it’s too noisy here and we might need to leave (I’m also 8 months pregnant). The manager was very rude and unprofessional. She said I’m threatening here and that she hadn’t been treated like this by anyone in 35 years. Honestly, I will never go back to a place where they treat their customers so poorly.

The food here is AMAZING. So many unique and delicious options for savory and sweet palates alike. The service is super friendly and prompt. The price is what you'd expect for the neighborhood, which is a little pricey in my book, so just go there knowing you'll spend in the range of $20 per person for breakfast and be ok with that. Well worth the money.
Food is delicious. Its a nice cafe with great food options
Great food great service
Delicious!

Stopped here with friends for breakfast because there was no line and getting 7 people seated was tough everywhere else.  This place felt like a typical diner with average coffee. I didn't feel that the price reflected the quality of the food well. The food wasn't amazing so I wouldn't come back.
Awesome staff and food to boot
Great breakfast place! On recommendation from our waitress, I had the Pumpkin pancakes and they were delicious!
The staff is so friendly and the food was great.   I'm glad I stopped by here for breakfast this morning.
Great food and lovely service
solid

Definitely my favorite place for brunch. I'm a brunch lover and I'm addicted to their food. Its a big restaurant as well so you never really have to wait in line. If you haven't gone yet, you are missing out. Pumpkin pancakes and the pesto skillets are the bomb!!!
Eh

Probably my favorite brunch restaurant in Chicago. I frequented it often when I used to live in the neighborhood a few years ago (Lincoln Park). Whenever I visit, I always try to visit this location specifically for brunch. It’s just a very cozy neighborhood sort of joint. They have some solid regular diner stuff on the menu and do some seasonal menu change-ups for specials. Also, I’m always fascinated that some of the same staff has been there over the 10 years I have been frequenting the restaurant (both when living there and when visiting). Adds to the neighborhood feel.

We were seated after a 20 minute wait.  Fine.  After we ordered we waited 50 minutes for our food.   One of us had to leave.  When it finally appeared it was bland at best, mis-ordered, ungarnished.  Other diners who were seated after us got their food ahead of us.   I left a big tip as I assumed it was not the waiters fault.  I won't be back.
Great and cozy place. The service was excellent and the portions are superb. Loved it ♥
Large portions of very good breakfast food. We'll be back. Great prices.

My husbands family loves coming here. This is the second time I've been here and it is a great atmosphere. I did not catch our waitress name but she was awesome! If you are a bread person then try the "Sweet Summer Trio" and you might want to share the sweetness with another. You can never go wrong with (my personal favorite) sweet potatoes fries!! Love it and you will enjoy it too.
Well done! This a great little breakfast joint that has some great omelets to try!
This place reminds me of a NJ diner in the best way possible! Great food, fast service, and overall a great brunch spot.
Great breakfast. BYOB. Love this place.
The staff is a little rude and the food is mediocre. I ordered the chilaquiles which I do not recommend.

Outstanding outpost of the Nookies empire.  Staff are pleasant, service is efficient, and the food is always good - especially the skillets and the specials.  If you go on the weekend expect a wait unless you arrive before 9am.

Love Nookies! My wife had this amazing stuffed French toast and I had the Dixie Benedict (no photo of mine as I inhaled it). The staff was great, the food cooked perfectly and quickly. Def highly recommend for a great brunch!

Excellent!!! We had a wrap and a scramble.  Both were flavorful.  Excellent friendly service.  The twins have been here for 33 years and just run things so smoothly, welcoming, excellent food and service... What more could anyone want?

This place was SO good! Not only did they accommodate the large and loud party of 8 I was with, but the food was really great. So great we came back the next day as well! Excellent service and terrific food!

This is a small little breakfast/brunch restaurant with tons of delicious options to choose from. Not one person wasn't happy with their meal and everyone walked away full and satisfied. I normally have a recommendation for restaurants but there really isn't anything I would change about this place. The wait staff was quick and very fast at getting anything we needed to the table
Really good diner food,very casual and many healthy options !!
Solid food, fast service, and a short wait to get your food. They could have been friendlier but maybe that is the price you pay for moving people in and out quickly.
A staple for breakfast and hangover cure. All the favorites on the menu. Worth the wait even if they make you wait on the sidewalk.
I had a delicious and HUGE omelette!! Service was great
Great byob diner. We go here for breakfast or brunch almost every weekend.
Breakfast here was amazing! You can bring in your own sparkling wine to make mimosas too!
Great food and service! Loved this place.
Delicious
Best breakfast in Lincoln Park!
Solid brunch menu. Food is great. Staff is super nice. Great spot for brunch/lunch!
Big plates.
Saturday morning favorite!
Cheddar grits always!! Nice local spot to grab a quick bite.
Stuffed French toast!!! YUM
Love this place! Good food and service.
Cozy space with satisfying brunch food.

This places is always a good choice for breakfast. I usually get their trio option, which includes three smaller portions of different specials going on at the time.  Good amount of food for the price. Usually get seated within 10-15 minutes. Not a long wait time.  The atmosphere is like any other diner. Check it out for their seasonal specials.
Very great service, quick and good food. Just a little pricey for breakfast
It's a classic diner with great breakfast and friendly servers who get to know you and your tastes. I go there for breakfast at least once a week - it's my second home!
Crunchy Croissant French toast layered with vanilla cream cheese and fresh strawberries, Wow worth every single calorie( p.s it’s not on the menu anymore but you could ask them about it)

Staff is fantastic. Food was honestly bland. Had the smoked brisket hash with some kind of tomato/bean salsa. I'm sure it had to do with the fact that we dined at the later part of the Sunday brunch hour so the quality wasn't quite there. Also coffee taste burnt as if it sat in its decanter for hours. It's fine. I'd come back to give the menu another shot.
Frankly, the food sucked. Soggy frozen hash browns, hollandaise sauce from a can, stale coffee. Don't eat here.
Good Cobb salad, and good price.
Green goddess skillet was delicious!
Lot of food for the money, BYOB is a plus. But food is meh. Good for large groups.
I'm not sure if they actually make their own English muffins but it sure tastes like they do - delicious!

Bright, pleasant atmosphere. The staff are all very friendly and the food is delicious (with surprisingly large portions which I honestly feel is rare for the city). Only real complaint is that requests were not taken at all. Apparently you can get blueberries with a pancake, but not with a waffle?
Nice spot for brunch.
It has just ok food, the bathrooms are disgusting.  The staff is ok. This is nothing special.
Best eggs Benedict I’ve ever had — the Paris Benedict is a must if you’re stopping in.
Great place. Very good portion sizes & good food
Great little place to relax and grab a bite to eat.
Quick and lots of food
Not great service and not great food. Atmosphere is meh.
Great diner food with a polite and friendly wait staff.

Great little spot for lunch or an early dinner. The food was very good and the server was friendly and quick. I'll definitely go back if I'm in the neighborhood, I didn't get to try everything that sounded good on the menu. The space is lit well and not terribly noisy too.
Nice people, great pancakes.
Great local cuisine here in Chicago ! This will become a regular when we are in town!

A go-to place for neighbourhood breakfasts with all the classics of the American Breakfast, from the healthy to the decadent. The two booths in the front are delicious when the morning sun streams in.  It's quiet, too in the mornings. A great place to start the day.
This is my boyfriend and my usual brunch place.
Bad coffee (probably Folgers).  Crepes were more like folded over pancakes and lacked any real discernable flavor. Server wasn't very attuned to my requests.
Nookies is a Lincoln Park staple.  I've never had poor service or a bad meal at Nookies Too!
The smokehouse is probably the best omelette I've ever had!
Pricey !!!
too bad stuff
Just another  Breakfast places trying to be  posh yuppie  whatever you wanna call it fancy was not  all that not going  back
Great good and service. Nice quaint diner atmosphere.
Standard diner fare. Crowded on weekends. Prefer the Old Town location to this one.

Service is great, but food not so much. Coffee is forgettable. I got a stuffed French toast with berries; it was not sweet but rather unusually tangy. I didn't want to box any to take home. I should have tried another breakfast spot in the area, not Nookies Too.
Chill place for breakfast and brunch. Ginormous servings could do without so much food per plate. Staff is very nice!
Great spot for breakfast.
Excellent southwest omelet, so so eggs benedict (bland hollandaise, over poached eggs, under toasted muffin), bad hash browns (no flavor at all)
Delicious scrambles and quick service.
Great small little place. It has a diner feel to it, except the food isn't your typical greasy diner fare.
(Translated by Google) Nice space and good drinks!  (Original) Espaço agradável e bons drinks!
I love this place! Fast friendly service, delicious and innovative diner food, and very cute decor. It can get crowded on the weekends, but that's how you know how good it is!
Staff is very nice and helpful. ....food is great.....👍
Great place to come pop a bottle of champagne and eat some delicious breakfast. YUMMMMMM!
Very good Benedict eggs. I got the Dixie Benedict and it was amazing. One of the best breakfast places in Lincoln park
Cute vibe, food was just ok. Staff are really sweet.
Decent place, but nothing to go too crazy over.  It's very basic diner food, good for a hangover I suppose. The service was okay.
Great neighborhood establishment! We've been going here for almost ten years now.  Have never been let down.
Great food!!!
Decent diner food. Service was good.
Average food, forgettable coffee and a bit over priced. Cute location.
To many loud college kids. Food is also kinda expensive for what you get
This place has a chic atmosphere and the food is good.
Always good food and service

A nice, spacious place to have brunch with friends! The sound level isn't too loud so you could have a conversation without having to yell. The dishes, both the seasonal items and regular items, are beautiful and taste delicious at your standard brunch price. I got the Green Goddess skillet which included veggies sauteed with hashbrowns in pesto sauce.
Great food. Venue is a little tight, and it is always full. But the food is great, service is quick.

This is a Chicago staple; however, I don't really understand why.  It's good, don't get me wrong. It has all your basic breakfast, brunch, and lunch dishes. They don't stray too much from the traditional menu. It has a very "diner-esque" atmosphere, where you sit quickly, you eat quickly, and you leave quickly. It's loud and tables are quite close together so sometimes you can't help but eavesdrop on your neighboring diners.  It's also nice that they are B.Y.O.B, but I don't know of a ton of people that would bother to bring drinks to a place like this. As I said, it's not the type of place you come for the atmosphere to sit and relax. It's good quality breakfast at standard prices. I've never had anything bad here, but I've also never had anything fantastic.
Great breakfast/brunch/lunch options. Very busy on the weekends, but worth the wait. Awesome seasonal menu.
Great breakfast and service in an adorable old diner feel.

Classic breakfast and diner food with an easy-to-read menu that's slimmer than the crazy books most diners have. Great brunch or late-night spot. I ordered huevos rancheros which was really good but not exceptional. Fair prices and lots of space.
Great breakfast! Original ideas.  A must try here in Chicago.  The eggs Benedict were alright.   Everything else was awesome.
Everything is delicious.  They also have season inspired specialties throughout the year that are must tries.
Huge portions and really friendly service at this breakfast/lunch diner in Lincoln Park. The egg sandwich on croissant is big enough for two people!
Really tasty, reasonably priced, good portions, can be busy
The chicken noodle soup was amazing!! Great food and nice staff!!
Their chicken noodle soup is the best I've ever had. Always pleasant service. A diner feel and food.
best breakfast restaurant in lincoln park for 30 years and friendly staff
Food was served quickly and was very good
Best place for breakfast in Lincoln Park.
Phenomenal breakfast. Not a single bad item in the menu.
Seriously, the Lincoln park location is one of the best brunches (for a great price) that you'll find, just don't be afraid to ask for your coffee refill!
The green goddess skillet was a great fuel source to power me through the day

I went to this place about two years ago.  From what I remember it was delicious.  I have been to Nookies more recently and that was delicious.  If you want some more casual breakfast the Nookie family of restaurants is a good place to start.

Nookies, too has good, homestyle comfort food.  There's nothing super fancy or unique about the food, but it's a good place to go if you want to traditional american cooking.  I normally prefer breakfast over lunch at Nookies.
Great place for breakfast! Coffee was wonderful, and corned beef hash was the best I've ever had! Definitely go!
Really tasty omelets. I like the asparagus myself and the wait is pretty short, even on busy days.
Excellent food. Very fun laid back atmosphere. Wait can be long on the weekends but it is always worth it. Never stick to one thing, there are too many good items. Try out the weekend specials.

Nookies Too has great food and good service. We went on a Saturday morning at 11 and there was no wait, which is unheard of in the area. Since it's a smaller joint it may not be the best for large parties, but the menu is concise and consistent so you know what to expect. Also has options for vegans and vegetarians!

This place was pretty good.  I've been to a Nookies before so I knew what to expect.  It was pretty slammed when I got there so my table by the door was pretty obscured for a while by the crowd waiting to get their names on the list.  Once the waiter found us though, it was fine.  I has the Huevos con Chorizo and that was awesome.  The portion was pretty huge though, truth be told, you'll pay for it.  I little pricey but worth it if you're looking for a big and delicious breakfast.  I got that with a side of hash browns and the total came to about $13.  The service was pretty solid and the guy kept our water glasses full and coffee cups hot.  Stop in for a brunch to take the hangovers away.
Go-to spot for brunch.  Large choice in the menu with excellent skillet options.
Amazing brunch.  Fun area.  Service is pleasant and efficient.  Make reservations because it gets full quick.
Great greasy spoon. We came on a Saturday morning, had a pretty short wait, and loved all our meals. The southwest eggs benedict was a big hit.
Best breakfast place in Chicago.I have my usual table every time I go there, don't even ask for a menu,they know what I want when I walk in.
If you love breakfast, Nookies is great! It's a great location on Lincoln. Make sure you have some time to spare, though, it's always busy weekend mornings--but for good reason!
Food is great, especially the omlettes.  The owner is very rude, and I would not go back for that reason.

Awesome food, service, and environment!  This place rocks!  The frittatas are excellent, the omelets are big and hearty, the pancakes are delicious, the sandwiches are good.  I highly recommend the Smoke House Frittata.  It is sweet, and smokey... a combination that I would find at a barbecue.  I know don't know how they pulled this off, but it is delicious!  I use to go to Clarkes for my late night fix...Nookies replaced them.

With dinner time approaching the grumbling of food was in need, and the desire to try a new diner was high. Being diner connoisseurs we whipped out our handy location based apps on our phones and started looking around the area. To our delight, a diner by the name of Nookies Too (a fun name) was rated 4-stars consistently across all their location and from hundreds of reviews. We deiced to give it a shot. My wife got the turkey club, myself the bacon cheeseburger. Wow – I now see why it is consistently rated 4 stars. The food was great and well priced, the staff was pleasant, and atmosphere quaint. We prefer the 50's diner motif most of the time, but it was still a great experience – will definitely be returning. Oh – and its 24 hours!
Egg & bacon breakfast sandwich is a must. Turkey rueben is as good.
People are nice, the food is good, but boy is it expensive for it being a simple brunch place. Also, service is really really slow at times.
